    {
        "content": "<p>The first one doesn't necessarily hold, it's consistent with ZFC that there exist sets <code>A, B</code> with <code>|A| &lt; |B|</code> but <code>2^|B| = 2^|A|</code> (<a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/a/6594/498835\">https://mathoverflow.net/a/6594/498835</a>).</p>",
        "id": 475051727,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1728189511
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"690858\">@Daniel Weber</span> Doesn't the first still hold with <code>|A| &lt; |B|</code> and  <code>2^|B| = 2^|A|</code>? That is, <code>2^|B| = 2^|A| -&gt; 2^|A| &lt;= 2^|B|</code> and <code>|A| &lt; |B| -&gt; |A| &lt;= |B|</code> so <code>2^|A| &lt;= 2^|B| -&gt; |A| &lt;= |B|</code> still hods.</p>",
