        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"315577\">Mac Malone</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Cardinal.20powers/near/475051901\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"690858\">Daniel Weber</span> Doesn't the first still hold with <code>|A| &lt; |B|</code> and  <code>2^|B| = 2^|A|</code>? That is, <code>2^|B| = 2^|A| -&gt; 2^|A| &lt;= 2^|B|</code> and <code>|A| &lt; |B| -&gt; |A| &lt;= |B|</code> so <code>2^|A| &lt;= 2^|B| -&gt; |A| &lt;= |B|</code> still hods.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Swap <code>A</code> and <code>B</code>, so <code>2^|B| &lt;= 2^|A|</code>, therefore <code>|B| &lt;= |A|</code>, but <code>|A| &lt; |B|</code>, contradiction</p>",
